@startuml DailyProblemClassification_SP_GetFromQueue
title CTS_DC_CustClassification_DailyScanPA_GetFromQueue - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam activityBorderColor #4CAF50

start

:Stored Procedure Called;
note right
  **SP Name**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_DailyScanPA_GetFromQueue
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsService (MySQL)
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (default)
  **Parameters**: None
  **Called From**: PADailyScanFromQueueGetCriteria
end note

:SELECT from CTSCustomerClassification_DailyPAQueue;
note right
  **Table**: CTSCustomerClassification_DailyPAQueue
  **Purpose**: Queue for PA customers to be processed daily
  
  **Queue Characteristics**:
  - FIFO (First In, First Out)
  - Populated by RealtimeClassification
  - Temporary storage for PA customers
  - Processed and then deleted
  
  **Queue Source**:
  - When RealtimeClassification identifies PA/PotentialPA
  - Customers with RelevantCategoryID IS NOT NULL
  - Inserted with current timestamp
end note

:Apply FIFO Logic;
note right
  **ORDER BY**: InsertedTime ASC
  - Get oldest customers first
  - Ensures fair processing order
  - Prevents customer starvation
end note

:Apply Batch Limit;
note right
  **LIMIT**: TOP 10000 (or configurable)
  - Prevent overwhelming system
  - Balance batch size vs throughput
  - Memory-efficient processing
  
  **Batch Size Considerations**:
  - Too large: Memory issues
  - Too small: Too many DB calls
  - Optimal: 5000-10000
end note

partition "Build Result Set" {
  :Get CustID;
  note right
    **CustID**: long
    - Primary customer identifier
    - Used for all subsequent operations
    - Foreign key to customer master
  end note

  :Get DWSportType;
  note right
    **DWSportType**: int (Sport Group)
    - Sport classification
    - Used for sport-specific logic
    - Affects PA calculation
    
    **Sport Types**:
    - 1: Soccer
    - 2: Basketball
    - 3: Other sports
    - etc.
  end note
}

:Return PADailyScanFromQueueEntity[];
note right
  **Return Type**: List<PADailyScanFromQueueEntity>
  
  **Entity Structure**:
  - CustID (long)
  - DWSportType (int)
  
  **Usage**:
  - Input to PA classification calculation
  - Identifies customers to process
  - Used in UpdateComplete to mark processed
end note

:Log Query Execution;
note right
  **Logging**:
  - Record count returned
  - Query execution time
  - Any errors/warnings
end note

if (Result set empty?) then (yes)
  :Return empty list;
  note right
    **No customers in queue**:
    - Normal during low traffic
    - Queue fully processed
    - No PA customers detected recently
  end note
else (no)
  :Return customer list;
  note right
    **Customers ready for PA classification**:
    - Will be processed in batches
    - Calculate PA losing performance
    - Insert PA probation classification
  end note
endif

:Complete;
stop

note bottom
  **Queue Management**:
  1. **Producer**: RealtimeClassification inserts PA customers
  2. **Consumer**: DailyProblemClassification processes queue
  3. **Cleanup**: UpdateComplete deletes processed customers
  
  **Queue Flow**:
  RealtimeClassification → DailyPAQueue → DailyProblemClassification → Delete from Queue
  
  **Performance**:
  - Indexed on InsertedTime for FIFO
  - Indexed on CustID for deletion
  - Regular cleanup prevents growth
  
  **Error Handling**:
  - Failed processing: Customer remains in queue
  - Retry on next job run
  - Alert if queue grows too large
end note

@enduml

